9 <a href="javascript:card_browser(241)">Slopes of Amon Hen</a>    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Strategy<br>
<br>
Shadow: Overwhelm Frodo<br>
<br>
I bid 1 because (A) I like to go second, (B) if my opponent bids 0 that means they like to go <br>
<br>
second, and (C) I don&#39;t play Sam in this deck. I will continue to go second until my site 6 is <br>
<br>
out. Then, generally, I will double move to 7 if my companionship has less than 3 wounds <br>
<br>
and/or a couple duplicate characters left in the deck. That sets me up for the final double <br>
<br>
move to site 9 if necessary.<br>
<br>
But my shadow side is built to win. What&#39;s the main problem with Nazgul decks? They are <br>
<br>
costly, and often there is not enough minions to dish out enough wounds (that&#39;s why Blade Tips <br>
<br>
are so useful). What&#39;s the main problem with Moria decks? They are prey to archery and Paths, <br>
<br>
and often they get beat in skirmishes.  So I combined the two focusing on cheap Moria swarm <br>
<br>
with twilight adding minions and conditions and beefy Nazgul who can use Relentless Charge to <br>
<br>
kill the archers before the archers kill me.<br>
<br>
Free People: Stayin Alive<br>
<br>
Basic Gandalf Loves Aragorn companionship with standard Legolas/Boromir backup. The <br>
<br>
companionship is slim, so Son of Denethor will make Frodo stronger, while Gandalf&#39;s SofS keeps <br>
<br>
the exertions to a minimum. SofS also helps the archers, of course, and 3 Butterburs makes <br>
<br>
sure you have one in your hand almost every turn.<br>
<br>
Lots of Possessions because bows and arrows, swords and armor, man that&#39;s where it&#39;s at! <br>
<br>
That&#39;ll keep me alive and beefy enough to double move if I have to keep up with a speedy <br>
<br>
opponent. <br>
<br>
A Big Deck! Yes, but with Scimitars, They Are Coming, Elrond & Ottar, AND Pilgrim Gandalf I <br>
<br>
don&#39;t have a problem getting near the bottom by site 9.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=22529"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=22529" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
